{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":2222,"text":"OK, first, some introductions."},{"time":5919,"text":"My mom, Jennie, took this picture."},{"time":9158,"text":"That's my dad, Frank, in the middle."},{"time":12139,"text":"And on his left, my sisters:"},{"time":14766,"text":"Mary Catherine, Judith Ann,\nTheresa Marie."},{"time":18815,"text":"John Patrick's sitting on his lap\nand Kevin Michael's on his right."},{"time":23739,"text":"And in the pale-blue windbreaker,"},{"time":26236,"text":"Susan Diane. Me."},{"time":29491,"text":"I loved growing up in a big family."},{"time":33159,"text":"And one of my favorite things\nwas picking names."},{"time":37924,"text":"But by the time child\nnumber seven came along,"},{"time":41393,"text":"we had nearly run out of middle names."},{"time":45075,"text":"It was a long deliberation"},{"time":46941,"text":"before we finally settled\non Jennifer Bridget."},{"time":52353,"text":"Every parent in this audience"},{"time":55108,"text":"knows the joy and excitement"},{"time":57756,"text":"of picking a new baby's name."},{"time":60913,"text":"And I was excited and thrilled"},{"time":62859,"text":"to help my mom in that special\nceremonial moment."}]},{"cues":[{"time":67824,"text":"But it's not like that everywhere."},{"time":71163,"text":"I travel a lot and I see a lot."},{"time":74273,"text":"But it took me by surprise to learn"},{"time":77390,"text":"in an area of Ethiopia,"},{"time":79593,"text":"parents delay picking the names\nfor their new babies"},{"time":83298,"text":"by a month or more."},{"time":85908,"text":"Why delay?"},{"time":88278,"text":"Why not take advantage\nof this special ceremonial time?"},{"time":92423,"text":"Well, they delay because they're afraid."},{"time":96007,"text":"They're afraid their baby will die."},{"time":99080,"text":"And this loss might be a little more\nbearable without a name."},{"time":105248,"text":"A face without a name might help them feel"},{"time":109177,"text":"just a little less attached."}]},{"cues":[{"time":113019,"text":"So here we are in one part of the world --"},{"time":115520,"text":"a time of joy, excitement,\ndreaming of the future of that child --"},{"time":120893,"text":"while in another world,"},{"time":123179,"text":"parents are filled with dread,"},{"time":126123,"text":"not daring to dream\nof a future for their child"},{"time":129722,"text":"beyond a few precious weeks."},{"time":132789,"text":"How can that be?"},{"time":135189,"text":"How can it be that 2.6 million babies"},{"time":140698,"text":"die around the world"},{"time":142516,"text":"before they're even one month old?"},{"time":145926,"text":"2.6 million."},{"time":149034,"text":"That's the population of Vancouver."},{"time":152512,"text":"And the shocking thing is:"},{"time":155043,"text":"Why?"},{"time":156365,"text":"In too many cases, we simply don't know."}]},{"cues":[{"time":161145,"text":"Now, I remember recently seeing\nan updated pie chart."},{"time":165295,"text":"And the pie chart was labeled,"},{"time":167487,"text":"\"Causes of death in children\nunder five worldwide.\""},{"time":171838,"text":"And there was a pretty big section\nof that pie chart, about 40 percent --"},{"time":175907,"text":"40 percent was labeled \"neonatal.\""},{"time":180077,"text":"Now, \"neonatal\" is not a cause of death."},{"time":182920,"text":"Neonatal is simply an adjective,"},{"time":185711,"text":"an adjective that means that the child\nis less than one month old."},{"time":191656,"text":"For me, \"neonatal\" said:\n\"We have no idea.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":197100,"text":"Now, I'm a scientist. I'm a doctor."},{"time":199294,"text":"I want to fix things."},{"time":201580,"text":"But you can't fix\nwhat you can't define."},{"time":206227,"text":"So our first step in restoring\nthe dreams of those parents"},{"time":211019,"text":"is to answer the question:"},{"time":213220,"text":"Why are babies dying?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":216359,"text":"So today, I want to talk\nabout a new approach,"},{"time":220118,"text":"an approach that I feel"},{"time":222079,"text":"will not only help us\nknow why babies are dying,"},{"time":227367,"text":"but is beginning to completely transform"},{"time":230768,"text":"the whole field of global health."},{"time":234235,"text":"It's called \"Precision Public Health.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":238615,"text":"For me, precision medicine comes\nfrom a very special place."},{"time":244894,"text":"I trained as a cancer doctor,\nan oncologist."},{"time":248079,"text":"I got into it because I wanted\nto help people feel better."},{"time":252491,"text":"But too often my treatments\nmade them feel worse."},{"time":257277,"text":"I still remember young women\nbeing driven to my clinic"},{"time":262550,"text":"by their moms --"},{"time":264611,"text":"adults, who had to be helped\ninto my exam room by their mothers."},{"time":270791,"text":"They were so weak"},{"time":271975,"text":"from the treatment I had given them."},{"time":275283,"text":"But at the time, in those front lines\nin the war on cancer,"},{"time":279507,"text":"we had few tools."},{"time":282030,"text":"And the tools we did have\ncouldn't differentiate"},{"time":285746,"text":"between the cancer cells\nthat we wanted to hit hard"},{"time":289670,"text":"and those healthy cells\nthat we wanted to preserve."},{"time":294663,"text":"And so the side effects that you're\nall very familiar with --"},{"time":297642,"text":"hair loss, being sick to your stomach,"},{"time":300500,"text":"having a suppressed immune system,\nso infection was a constant threat --"},{"time":305179,"text":"were always surrounding us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":308985,"text":"And then I moved\nto the biotechnology industry."},{"time":312269,"text":"And I got to work on a new approach\nfor breast cancer patients"},{"time":316373,"text":"that could do a better job\nof telling the healthy cells"},{"time":321398,"text":"from the unhealthy or cancer cells."},{"time":324566,"text":"It's a drug called Herceptin."},{"time":327343,"text":"And what Herceptin allowed us to do"},{"time":330603,"text":"is to precisely target\nHER2-positive breast cancer,"},{"time":337036,"text":"at the time, the scariest\nform of breast cancer."},{"time":340091,"text":"And that precision let us\nhit hard the cancer cells,"},{"time":344727,"text":"while sparing and being more\ngentle on the normal cells."},{"time":350441,"text":"A huge breakthrough."},{"time":352181,"text":"It felt like a miracle,"},{"time":355091,"text":"so much so that today,"},{"time":358064,"text":"we're harnessing all those tools --"},{"time":361156,"text":"big data, consumer monitoring,\ngene sequencing and more --"},{"time":366704,"text":"to tackle a broad variety of diseases."},{"time":371044,"text":"That's allowing us to target individuals"},{"time":376137,"text":"with the right remedies at the right time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":380731,"text":"Precision medicine\nrevolutionized cancer therapy."},{"time":385655,"text":"Everything changed."},{"time":388187,"text":"And I want everything to change again."},{"time":392214,"text":"So I've been asking myself:"},{"time":394490,"text":"Why should we limit"},{"time":396332,"text":"this smarter, more precise,\nbetter way to tackle diseases"},{"time":401165,"text":"to the rich world?"},{"time":404105,"text":"Now, don't misunderstand me --"},{"time":405641,"text":"I'm not talking about bringing\nexpensive medicines like Herceptin"},{"time":408991,"text":"to the developing world,"},{"time":410900,"text":"although I'd actually kind of like that."},{"time":413707,"text":"What I am talking about"},{"time":415696,"text":"is moving from this precise\ntargeting for individuals"},{"time":420088,"text":"to tackle public health problems"},{"time":422755,"text":"in populations."}]},{"cues":[{"time":426487,"text":"Now, OK, I know probably\nyou're thinking, \"She's crazy."},{"time":431094,"text":"You can't do that. That's too ambitious.\""},{"time":434830,"text":"But here's the thing:"},{"time":437180,"text":"we're already doing this in a limited way,"},{"time":440502,"text":"and it's already starting\nto make a big difference."}]},{"cues":[{"time":444606,"text":"So here's what's happening."},{"time":446952,"text":"Now, I told you I trained\nas a cancer doctor."},{"time":449566,"text":"But like many, many doctors\nwho trained in San Francisco in the '80s,"},{"time":454039,"text":"I also trained as an AIDS doctor."},{"time":457077,"text":"It was a terrible time."},{"time":459504,"text":"AIDS was a death sentence."},{"time":462385,"text":"All my patients died."},{"time":465329,"text":"Now, things are better,"},{"time":467257,"text":"but HIV/AIDS remains\na terrible global challenge."},{"time":472473,"text":"Worldwide, about 17 million women\nare living with HIV."},{"time":478744,"text":"We know that when these women\nbecome pregnant,"},{"time":482065,"text":"they can transfer the virus to their baby."},{"time":486551,"text":"We also know in the absence of therapy,"},{"time":488827,"text":"half those babies will not survive\nuntil the age of two."},{"time":493446,"text":"But we know that antiretroviral therapy\ncan virtually guarantee"},{"time":498607,"text":"that she will not transmit\nthe virus to the baby."},{"time":501860,"text":"So what do we do?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":503708,"text":"Well, a one-size-fits-all approach,\nkind of like that blast of chemo,"},{"time":508294,"text":"would mean we test and treat\nevery pregnant woman in the world."},{"time":511952,"text":"That would do the job."},{"time":513889,"text":"But it's just not practical."},{"time":517223,"text":"So instead, we target those areas\nwhere HIV rates are the highest."},{"time":523444,"text":"We know in certain countries\nin sub-Saharan Africa"},{"time":527845,"text":"we can test and treat pregnant women\nwhere rates are highest."},{"time":532794,"text":"This precision approach\nto a public health problem"},{"time":535976,"text":"has cut by nearly half"},{"time":538401,"text":"HIV transmission from mothers to baby"},{"time":541180,"text":"in the last five years."}]},{"cues":[{"time":543485,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":548945,"text":"Screening pregnant women\nin certain areas in the developing world"},{"time":554031,"text":"is a powerful example"},{"time":557159,"text":"of how precision public health\ncan change things on a big scale."}]},{"cues":[{"time":564452,"text":"So ..."},{"time":566213,"text":"How do we do that?"},{"time":567414,"text":"We can do that because we know."},{"time":569896,"text":"We know who to target,"},{"time":572238,"text":"what to target,"},{"time":573949,"text":"where to target and how to target."},{"time":576685,"text":"And that, for me, are the important \nelements of precision public health:"},{"time":581780,"text":"who, what, where and how."}]},{"cues":[{"time":585814,"text":"But let's go back\nto the 2.6 million babies"},{"time":589739,"text":"who die before they're one month old."},{"time":591780,"text":"Here's the problem: we just don't know."},{"time":594753,"text":"It may seem unbelievable,"},{"time":597241,"text":"but the way we figure out\nthe causes of infant mortality"},{"time":602128,"text":"in those countries\nwith the highest infant mortality"},{"time":605163,"text":"is a conversation with mom."},{"time":607948,"text":"A health worker asks a mom\nwho has just lost her child,"},{"time":612350,"text":"\"Was the baby vomiting?\nDid they have a fever?\""},{"time":616043,"text":"And that conversation may take place"},{"time":618016,"text":"as long as three months\nafter the baby has died."},{"time":622951,"text":"Now, put yourself\nin the shoes of that mom."},{"time":627239,"text":"It's a heartbreaking,\nexcruciating conversation."},{"time":631833,"text":"And even worse -- it's not that helpful,"},{"time":635635,"text":"because we might know\nthere was a fever or vomiting,"},{"time":638612,"text":"but we don't know why."},{"time":641171,"text":"So in the absence of knowing\nthat knowledge,"},{"time":644677,"text":"we cannot prevent that mom, that family,"},{"time":647683,"text":"or other families in that community"},{"time":649805,"text":"from suffering the same tragedy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":652804,"text":"But what if we applied\na precision public health approach?"},{"time":657064,"text":"Let's say, for example,"},{"time":658482,"text":"we find out in certain areas of Africa"},{"time":661440,"text":"that babies are dying\nbecause of a bacterial infection"},{"time":665210,"text":"transferred from the mother to the baby,"},{"time":667781,"text":"known as Group B streptococcus."},{"time":670999,"text":"In the absence of treatment,\nmom has a seven times higher chance"},{"time":676535,"text":"that her next baby will die."},{"time":680124,"text":"Once we define the problem,\nwe can prevent that death"},{"time":684049,"text":"with something as cheap\nand safe as penicillin."},{"time":689894,"text":"We can do that because then we'll know."},{"time":693034,"text":"And that's the point:"},{"time":694590,"text":"once we know, we can bring\nthe right interventions"},{"time":698050,"text":"to the right population\nin the right places"},{"time":701613,"text":"to save lives."}]},{"cues":[{"time":704973,"text":"With this approach,\nand with these interventions"},{"time":708749,"text":"and others like them,"},{"time":710798,"text":"I have no doubt"},{"time":712533,"text":"that a precision public health approach"},{"time":715104,"text":"can help our world achieve\nour 15-year goal."},{"time":719423,"text":"And that would translate\ninto a million babies' lives saved"},{"time":723776,"text":"every single year."},{"time":726253,"text":"One million babies every single year."}]},{"cues":[{"time":731706,"text":"And why would we stop there?"},{"time":734319,"text":"A much more powerful approach\nto public health --"},{"time":737640,"text":"imagine what might be possible."},{"time":740912,"text":"Why couldn't we more effectively\ntackle malnutrition?"},{"time":745643,"text":"Why wouldn't we prevent\ncervical cancer in women?"},{"time":750832,"text":"And why not eradicate malaria?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":753674,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":754699,"text":"Yes, clap for that!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":755936,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":759888,"text":"So, you know, I live\nin two different worlds,"},{"time":762755,"text":"one world populated by scientists,"},{"time":766590,"text":"and another world populated\nby public health professionals."},{"time":771319,"text":"The promise of precision public health"},{"time":773771,"text":"is to bring these two worlds together."},{"time":776876,"text":"But you know, we all live in two worlds:"},{"time":781254,"text":"the rich world and the poor world."},{"time":785760,"text":"And what I'm most excited about\nabout precision public health"},{"time":789634,"text":"is bridging these two worlds."},{"time":793051,"text":"Every day in the rich world,"},{"time":796095,"text":"we're bringing incredible\ntalent and tools --"},{"time":799374,"text":"everything at our disposal --"},{"time":801357,"text":"to precisely target diseases\nin ways I never imagined"},{"time":806294,"text":"would be possible."},{"time":808152,"text":"Surely, we can tap into\nthat kind of talent and tools"},{"time":813192,"text":"to stop babies dying in the poor world."},{"time":817201,"text":"If we did,"},{"time":819274,"text":"then every parent would have\nthe confidence"},{"time":823355,"text":"to name their child\nthe moment that child is born,"},{"time":828746,"text":"daring to dream that that child's life\nwill be measured in decades,"},{"time":834498,"text":"not days."}]},{"cues":[{"time":836330,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":837505,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}